cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a neural network architecture for machine learning from 3D point clouds, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of spherical convolutional kernels and the focus on identifying local geometric structures suggest a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of space partitioning and the octree structure suggest a focus on computational geometry (cs.GR). Finally, the use of efficient learning with high resolution point clouds suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
